if system's locked like this, is there a way to enter some linux command in a pty(?) like alacritty to switch vc(?). do i have the terms right?

You have the terminology almost perfect!

VC (Virtual Console): Correct. This is the "full-screen" terminal (tty1, tty2).

PTY (Pseudo-terminal): Correct. This is what runs inside your terminal emulator (Alacritty) or a multiplexer like tmux.

The Action: You are wanting to "switch" the active VT from the command line.

Yes, you can absolutely do this. You don't need to physically claw-grip your keyboard to switch.

The Command: chvt
The "sophisticated" command you’re looking for is chvt (Change Virtual Terminal).

If you are inside Alacritty (a PTY) and want to force the entire system to switch to TTY3 (a VC), you run:

Bash
sudo chvt 3
Why do you need sudo?
Switching the active console is considered a "privileged" action. If any random process could switch your screen, a malicious script could constantly flip your TTYs back and forth, effectively "blinding" you in a prank that never ends.

How it works (The Plumbing)
When you run chvt, you are sending an instruction to the Kernel's Console Driver.

Alacritty (PTY) sends the command to the shell.

The shell executes chvt.

The Kernel receives the VT_ACTIVATE request.

The Kernel tells the GPU: "Stop rendering the buffer for TTY1 (Hyprland) and start rendering the buffer for TTY3."

Is there a "User-Level" way? (The openvt trick)
If you want to run a command on a different TTY without even switching to it, you use openvt.

For example, if you want to start a system update on TTY2 while staying inside Hyprland on TTY1:

Bash
sudo openvt -s -c 2 -- python3 -m my_long_script.py
The -s flag tells the system to "switch" to it immediately, but you can omit it if you just want the command to run in the background on that specific console.

Summary of Terms for your "Mental Wiki"
TTY: The generic term for the device.

VC / VT: The specific "screen" (tty1-6).

PTY/PTS: The "fake" terminal inside your GUI (Alacritty).

chvt: The command to teleport between them.

